 effusive, slangy style of the young prince and the rhetorical flourishes of his master, the letters between Marcus and Fronto will rightfully be reconsidered as key documents in the study of the history of sexuality and classics.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aLove-letterszRome. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh1 aFronto, Marcus Cornelius, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aRichlin, Amy.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013z978311063538640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226713021423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780226713021.jpg  a978-3-11-063538-6  University of Chicago Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles